      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD ODDS KEONA (3) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where she gave a sight, finishing third (22.75) and beaten 1.5 lengths over 388m at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Expected to feature in the finish again. PITMAN GO WELL (1) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest hitting the ground running with a fast early sectional but finishing in the minors again when second (22.55) over 388m at this track. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Expected to feature. JEANNA (2) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 8 length second (22.92) in a Grade 5 at this track. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Will give a great sight again. BERNARDO'S BELLE (7) is a last start winner who rates one of the chances again.",
